HEADWORD: Hyperæmia
<hw>Hy`per*⟦ae⟧"mi*a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr.
Gr. <grk>"ype`r</grk> over + <grk>a"i^ma</grk> blood.]</ety>
<fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A superabundance or congestion of blood in an
organ or part of the body.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Active hyper⟦ae⟧mia</b></col>, <cd>congestion due to
increased flow of blood to a part.</cd> -- <col><b>Passive
hyper⟦ae⟧mia</b></col>, <cd>interchange due to obstruction in the return
of blood from a part.</cd></cs></p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Hy`per*⟦ae⟧"mic</wf> <pr>(#)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hyperaesthesia</ent>⟦br⟧
